{"questionId":"13820","questionHtml":"<p>Prove that there are two horizontal tangents to the general solution curve and state&nbsp;their equations, in terms of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c\">\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}y}}{{{\\text{d}}x}} = \\frac{{{y^2} - {x^2}}}{{2xy}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>y</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>(for horizontal tangents)&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}y}}{{{\\text{d}}x}} = 0\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( { \\Rightarrow {y^2} = {x^2}} \\right) \\Rightarrow y =&nbsp; \\pm x\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>y</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>±</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>using&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^2} + {y^2} = cx \\Rightarrow 2{x^2} = cx\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2{x^2} - cx = 0 \\Rightarrow x = \\frac{c}{2}\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1A1</strong></em> for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2{y^2} =&nbsp; \\pm cy\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>±</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>using implicit differentiation of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^2} + {y^2} = cx\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2x + 2y\\frac{{{\\text{d}}y}}{{{\\text{d}}x}} = c\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept differentiation of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = \\sqrt {cx - {x^2}} \">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msqrt>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>−</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}y}}{{{\\text{d}}x}} = 0 \\Rightarrow x = \\frac{c}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>tangents at&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = \\frac{c}{2},\\,\\,y =&nbsp; - \\frac{c}{2}\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>,</mo>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence there are two tangents&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^2} + {y^2} = cx\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {x - \\frac{c}{2}} \\right)^2} + {y^2} = \\frac{{{c^2}}}{4}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mfrac>\n            <mi>c</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>c</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>this is a circle radius&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\frac{c}{2}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mfrac>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> centre&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{c}{2},\\,\\,0} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>c</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>,</mo>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence there are two tangents&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>tangents at&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = \\frac{c}{2},\\,\\,y =&nbsp; - \\frac{c}{2}\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>,</mo>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13820","referenceCode":"19M.3.AHL.TZ0.Hca_5b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Prove that there are two horizontal tangents to the general solution curve and state their equations, in terms of c .","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.18—1st order DE’s – Euler method, variables separable, integrating factor, homogeneous DE using sub y=vx"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}